race.comment: DUHLATA (1) wasn't far away two back then thrown into open class in the Murtoa Cup when fifth. Big class drop and gets a chance to bounce back. GREATESTOFEASE (8) ran on hard at Manangatang on Cup day to score with ease. This is harder but back in form and can race closer. Another who can be handier to the front is COSMOS FACTORY (4) who has performed well at two runs for a new yard. Was always known as a backmarker but has been sitting close and going well. Among the chances. JOHNNY CIGAR (6) was disappointing last time but the run prior in the south-east was an effortless Naracoorte win. Rates highly on that effort and can bounce back.
